1
00:00:01,130 --> 00:00:03,930
Hey, all you viewers out there!

2
00:00:03,930 --> 00:00:07,270
When you're watchin' Fairy Tail, make sure to keep the room nice and bright,

3
00:00:07,270 --> 00:00:09,280
and sit back from the screen, 'kay?

4
00:00:10,570 --> 00:00:12,900
Previously on Fairy Tail!

5
00:00:12,900 --> 00:00:15,180
The Phantom Lord guild came to attack!

6
00:00:15,180 --> 00:00:19,700
Erza defended against the Magic Focusing Cannon, Jupiter, and she was knocked out of commission.

7
00:00:19,700 --> 00:00:24,650
Now we're infiltrating Phantom's guild in order to destroy the cannon!

8
00:00:25,170 --> 00:00:27,880
That's right, we can do it!

9
00:00:27,880 --> 00:00:30,910
Let's go for even more who-knows-what!!

10
00:00:30,910 --> 00:00:36,420
The door to mystery is right in front of us

11
00:00:36,420 --> 00:00:39,100
The whole world's a wonderland

12
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:42,140
which we're already wondering!!!

13
00:00:42,140 --> 00:00:47,240
This excitement gets my heart racing

14
00:00:47,240 --> 00:00:48,570
It's wonderful!

15
00:00:48,570 --> 00:00:51,440
Who am I, I wonder?

16
00:00:51,440 --> 00:00:54,240
What is real, I wonder?

17
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:58,840
Why can't I see tomorrow, I wonder?

18
00:00:59,970 --> 00:01:05,070
The only part leveling up is my curiosity

19
00:01:05,070 --> 00:01:10,900
We can't just throw away our daily life together, right?

20
00:01:11,590 --> 00:01:18,590
Tell me! S. O. W.

21
00:01:19,910 --> 00:01:24,270
Living itself will be our training!

22
00:01:24,270 --> 00:01:27,330
So, we can make it!

23
00:01:27,330 --> 00:01:30,160
Let's search for even more who-knows-what!

24
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:35,820
We can't be satisfied with just the normal answers

25
00:01:35,820 --> 00:01:38,630
This magical wonder life

26
00:01:38,630 --> 00:01:41,450
Our future is wondering!!!

27
00:01:41,450 --> 00:01:46,550
We'll do our best living our life

28
00:01:46,550 --> 00:01:48,590
the way we want to!

29
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:51,880
Let's wondering!!!

30
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:59,550
Natsu!

31
00:01:59,550 --> 00:02:01,540
Jupiter has activated!

32
00:02:01,540 --> 00:02:02,800
I know, geez!

33
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:03,810
Take this...

34
00:02:03,810 --> 00:02:05,470
Blue Fire!

35
00:02:09,980 --> 00:02:12,180
Ooh, that's cold!

36
00:02:12,180 --> 00:02:14,180
Never eaten fire like that before.

37
00:02:14,180 --> 00:02:18,470
I see... So you're the Dragon Slayer I've heard rumors about.

38
00:02:18,470 --> 00:02:21,740
This means that we're both at a disadvantage.

39
00:02:21,740 --> 00:02:22,530
Oh, yeah?

40
00:02:22,530 --> 00:02:25,120
Fire won't work on either of us.

41
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:26,920
Don't go decidin' that yourself!

42
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:28,470
I haven't even hit you yet!

43
00:02:28,470 --> 00:02:31,460
Exactly! I can't be hit by fire!

44
00:02:32,330 --> 00:02:34,120
Then how about this...

45
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:34,920
Fire Dragon's...

46
00:02:35,170 --> 00:02:38,170
All fire is under my control!

47
00:02:38,170 --> 00:02:39,550
...Spit!

48
00:02:39,830 --> 00:02:41,200
Soaked...

49
00:02:42,310 --> 00:02:43,550
You fell for it!

50
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:48,450
So No One Sees the Tears

51
00:02:50,640 --> 00:02:53,310
2 minutes until Jupiter fires.

52
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:55,230
This isn't good!

53
00:02:55,230 --> 00:02:57,790
Jupiter's gonna fire!

54
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:57,790
Why, you...

55
00:02:57,790 --> 00:02:58,990
You tricked me!

56
00:02:58,990 --> 00:03:00,860
Orange Fire!

57
00:03:01,820 --> 00:03:05,260
Didn't you see? I <i>eat</i> fire!

58
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:09,050
It stinks!

59
00:03:09,370 --> 00:03:10,780
My nose!

60
00:03:11,370 --> 00:03:14,130
That fire's the smell of a mop drenched with curdled milk!

61
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:15,910
You dirty little...

62
00:03:15,910 --> 00:03:17,380
Well, you started it!

63
00:03:19,550 --> 00:03:22,220
1 minute until Jupiter fires.

64
00:03:22,220 --> 00:03:25,160
Natsu! Calm down!

65
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:25,800
Quiet!

66
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:29,310
Whoa, there... Giving up on magic and using your fists?

67
00:03:29,590 --> 00:03:33,100
In that case I, with my katana, have the advantage!

68
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:44,930
Too bad.

69
00:03:44,930 --> 00:03:48,100
A scratch like that can't destroy such a large lacrima.

70
00:03:48,100 --> 00:03:49,620
Oh, is that so?

71
00:03:51,010 --> 00:03:53,080
Then how about this?

72
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:56,790
Honestly, you don't learn a thing, do you?

73
00:04:01,910 --> 00:04:06,010
Why, that... He expanded the fire enough so I'd get hit by it?

74
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:13,310
Only 30 seconds left.

75
00:04:13,590 --> 00:04:15,310
This isn't looking good.

76
00:04:15,310 --> 00:04:16,900
What's taking Natsu so long?

77
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:18,400
This isn't good!

78
00:04:18,400 --> 00:04:19,300
This isn't good!

79
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:22,510
20 second until Jupiter fires.

80
00:04:23,110 --> 00:04:25,220
That won't work a second time.

81
00:04:25,220 --> 00:04:29,420
I told you already... All fire is under my control!

82
00:04:32,330 --> 00:04:33,080
What the...

83
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:35,200
It won't move!

84
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:37,560
That fire... It couldn't be...

85
00:04:38,210 --> 00:04:39,880
He's resisting my control?

86
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:42,840
Did he figure that out <i>during</i> the fight?

87
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:44,630
Natsu!

88
00:04:44,630 --> 00:04:49,010
How dare you move <i>my</i> fire!

89
00:04:51,540 --> 00:04:53,940
What does it matter as long as you don't hit me?

90
00:04:53,940 --> 00:04:56,980
3... 2... 1...

91
00:04:56,980 --> 00:04:57,860
What?

92
00:04:57,860 --> 00:05:01,020
I wasn't aimin' for you from the start!

93
00:05:12,870 --> 00:05:14,360
Look at that!

94
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:15,570
The cannon!

95
00:05:15,570 --> 00:05:16,880
They did it!

96
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:19,630
They managed to destroy Jupiter!

97
00:05:23,330 --> 00:05:25,100
Incredible...

98
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:27,680
Look here, bud.

99
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:31,230
Fire ain't gonna listen to people telling it what to do.

100
00:05:31,230 --> 00:05:34,420
It responds to your heart's will.

101
00:05:34,420 --> 00:05:35,680
I see...

102
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:38,980
Without defeating him and overcoming his control of fire,

103
00:05:38,980 --> 00:05:41,770
it would have been impossible to destroy Jupiter!

104
00:05:41,770 --> 00:05:45,040
I guess I was the one who wasn't thinking calmly.

105
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:48,030
Not bad there, Natsu!

106
00:05:48,030 --> 00:05:50,070
Without Jupiter, we'll manage things somehow!

107
00:05:50,070 --> 00:05:51,620
Now's our chance to push them back!

108
00:05:51,620 --> 00:05:53,550
Wipe out the enemy!

109
00:05:57,350 --> 00:06:00,210
The bratty children got their spunk back.

110
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,590
Start up the giant.

111
00:06:02,590 --> 00:06:05,900
You can't manipulate my fire any longer!

112
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:09,090
It's your turn to get blown to smithereens, Phantom!

113
00:06:11,510 --> 00:06:12,360
Stabilizing elements!

114
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:14,470
Activating lateral balance lacrima.

115
00:06:12,790 --> 00:06:15,100
Wizards in dangerous areas, evacuate immediately.

116
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:16,840
It awakens!

117
00:06:25,930 --> 00:06:27,380
What the... what?

118
00:06:27,380 --> 00:06:28,740
It's tilting!

119
00:06:28,990 --> 00:06:31,020
They plan to do that?!

120
00:06:31,020 --> 00:06:33,900
This area isn't laterally stabilized!

121
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:35,290
Laterally?

122
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:41,170
Now what are they planning?

123
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:47,880
Hip joints stabilized! Standing up!

124
00:06:49,340 --> 00:06:51,320
The giant has awakened!

125
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:54,140
It's over for you guys!

126
00:06:54,140 --> 00:06:56,050
Natsu, hang in there!

127
00:06:56,050 --> 00:06:56,560
No way...

128
00:06:56,860 --> 00:06:58,540
What the heck is that?

129
00:06:58,540 --> 00:07:00,380
I mean, seriously...

130
00:07:00,380 --> 00:07:02,960
It's a giant... A magical giant!

131
00:07:04,650 --> 00:07:08,030
You should grovel and beg for forgiveness, you damn kids.

132
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:11,000
Then you will learn your place!

133
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:15,930
Feast on despair until the end of your pitiful lives!

134
00:07:15,930 --> 00:07:17,450
What should we do?

135
00:07:22,820 --> 00:07:24,380
The Shades are coming back!

136
00:07:24,380 --> 00:07:27,460
A giant and ghosts? What are they doing?

137
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:29,830
We'll concentrate on the Shades!

138
00:07:29,830 --> 00:07:32,750
I'm sure that Natsu will find a way to stop the giant!

139
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:34,450
Sure, but...

140
00:07:34,450 --> 00:07:35,930
Natsu and transportation...

141
00:07:39,220 --> 00:07:41,330
Natsu, sheesh!

142
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:43,510
You get motion sick?

143
00:07:43,850 --> 00:07:46,230
You can't eat fire as you are now.

144
00:07:46,230 --> 00:07:49,600
I'll burn you to a crisp with my strongest magic!

145
00:07:50,270 --> 00:07:51,860
Natsu!

146
00:07:51,860 --> 00:07:54,740
I'll blow you to bits, Dragon Slayer!

147
00:07:54,740 --> 00:07:55,570
...Uh...

148
00:07:57,230 --> 00:07:58,870
What the...

149
00:07:59,130 --> 00:08:00,250
If you're a man...

150
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:02,290
...fly to the heavens and become a star!

151
00:08:02,290 --> 00:08:04,790
What is that supposed to mean?

152
00:08:05,190 --> 00:08:06,430
You guys...

153
00:08:06,430 --> 00:08:07,750
Too cool!

154
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:09,870
Gray, Elfman!

155
00:08:09,870 --> 00:08:12,850
Mr. Natsu is so pitiful, he is.

156
00:08:12,850 --> 00:08:16,300
If you're a man, then <i>you</i> should make the <i>car</i> sick!

157
00:08:16,300 --> 00:08:19,320
So, are these the remains of Jupiter?

158
00:08:19,320 --> 00:08:20,730
Aye!

159
00:08:20,730 --> 00:08:22,470
Good job there.

160
00:08:22,470 --> 00:08:24,690
It's stopped all of a sudden!

161
00:08:24,690 --> 00:08:27,400
I'll take a look outside!

162
00:08:30,450 --> 00:08:32,210
Letters? No...

163
00:08:32,210 --> 00:08:33,530
That's... No way!

164
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,250
It's a magic circle!

165
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:38,700
That magic circle is for Abyss Break!

166
00:08:39,010 --> 00:08:41,280
That's one of the forbidden magics!

167
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:44,440
At that size, we're in big trouble!

168
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:47,580
Magnolia itself will be destroyed in the wave of darkness!

169
00:08:48,580 --> 00:08:49,840
...is what they said!

170
00:08:50,140 --> 00:08:52,740
What the heck?! I don't believe it!

171
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:56,790
We have no choice but to split up and find the power moving this giant.

172
00:08:56,790 --> 00:08:58,760
Man... Out of the frying pan and into the fire....

173
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:01,390
Okay then, let's do it!

174
00:09:01,390 --> 00:09:02,390
Yeah!

175
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:08,280
Mira, how long until that magic spell activates.

176
00:09:08,280 --> 00:09:10,270
About 10 minutes, I think.

177
00:09:10,270 --> 00:09:12,670
We have to destroy its power source somehow.

178
00:09:12,670 --> 00:09:16,070
Our men inside must be thinking the same thing.

179
00:09:16,070 --> 00:09:18,220
There're people other than Natsu in there?

180
00:09:18,220 --> 00:09:19,700
Gray and Elfman.

181
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:21,130
Elfman?

182
00:09:21,130 --> 00:09:21,830
But, why?

183
00:09:22,110 --> 00:09:24,880
Why? He also wants to...

184
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:27,700
It's no use! Elfman can't fight.

185
00:09:27,700 --> 00:09:29,170
You know that, Cana!

186
00:09:29,170 --> 00:09:30,890
He can fight.

187
00:09:30,890 --> 00:09:33,390
He helped us when we raided them before, remember?

188
00:09:33,390 --> 00:09:38,350
Fighting with their lackeys is one thing, but if he goes up against their big guns...

189
00:09:38,350 --> 00:09:40,160
As he is now, Elfman can't...

190
00:09:41,470 --> 00:09:43,580
Hey, Mira...

191
00:09:43,580 --> 00:09:49,180
When that happened, you, Elfman, and everyone too...

192
00:09:49,180 --> 00:09:50,730
We all suffered a deep wound.

193
00:09:51,350 --> 00:09:55,560
However, in his own way, he's forced himself to move forward.

194
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:57,090
I know you realize this.

195
00:10:01,070 --> 00:10:04,330
Elfman... moved forward...

196
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:07,090
Lisanna...

197
00:10:10,270 --> 00:10:13,170
I also have to move forward!

198
00:10:16,130 --> 00:10:17,110
Hey!

199
00:10:17,110 --> 00:10:18,820
Mira, what are you doing?

200
00:10:18,820 --> 00:10:19,970
Don't! It's dangerous!

201
00:10:23,310 --> 00:10:24,310
Oh, my...

202
00:10:24,610 --> 00:10:27,520
You people are looking for me, right?

203
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:30,170
Stop your attack on the guild this instant!

204
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:34,150
This should at least buy everyone some time.

205
00:10:35,020 --> 00:10:36,140
Master!

206
00:10:36,140 --> 00:10:37,610
That's...

207
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:39,850
Begone...

208
00:10:39,850 --> 00:10:41,920
You damn impostor!

209
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:43,100
But...

210
00:10:44,810 --> 00:10:48,130
I knew from the start!

211
00:10:48,130 --> 00:10:51,890
I knew that Lucy wasn't there.

212
00:10:52,540 --> 00:10:53,710
Damn it...

213
00:10:57,560 --> 00:11:01,530
How powerless am I... truly...

214
00:11:03,950 --> 00:11:08,980
The Man, Elfman, will protect Fairy Tail with his life!

215
00:11:10,390 --> 00:11:11,190
Oui?

216
00:11:14,260 --> 00:11:15,480
Salut!

217
00:11:15,910 --> 00:11:17,740
An Element 4?

218
00:11:18,130 --> 00:11:21,790
Don't worry. Elfman can fight.

219
00:11:21,790 --> 00:11:25,000
Because he's a Fairy Tail Wizard, too!

220
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:38,460
Elfman...

221
00:11:40,410 --> 00:11:41,740
Oh, no!

222
00:11:42,190 --> 00:11:43,300
Mira!

223
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:50,140
I detest girls like this who try to deceive me.

224
00:11:50,140 --> 00:11:54,400
Witness your friend's final moments as I crush her slowly.

225
00:11:55,330 --> 00:11:56,850
Mira!

226
00:11:56,850 --> 00:11:58,420
Damn it, what the hell!

227
00:11:58,420 --> 00:12:00,650
Mira-chan!

228
00:12:00,650 --> 00:12:02,820
They've got to hurry and stop that giant!

229
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:06,440
Natsu... Gray... Elfman!

230
00:12:07,470 --> 00:12:11,930
My name is Sol! Please call me Monsieur Sol!

231
00:12:11,930 --> 00:12:15,710
Perfect timing. I'll force you to tell me how to stop this giant.

232
00:12:15,930 --> 00:12:18,290
Beast Arm!

233
00:12:18,640 --> 00:12:19,880
Black Bull!

234
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:23,010
Oh? Just your right arm? Are you sure?

235
00:12:23,630 --> 00:12:27,530
It seems that the rumors are true.

236
00:12:27,530 --> 00:12:30,180
I've had enough of your blabbing!

237
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:35,560
Didn't you have a little sister?

238
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:38,990
Sable Dance!

239
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:44,700
Roche Concerto!

240
00:12:47,300 --> 00:12:49,160
Non, non, non...

241
00:12:50,810 --> 00:12:52,020
Salut!

242
00:12:52,020 --> 00:12:53,960
You really creep me out.

243
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:55,130
Non, non, non...

244
00:12:55,130 --> 00:12:57,770
Three nons and you're in quite a sad state.

245
00:12:57,770 --> 00:13:00,140
Unhand me, Monster Sol!

246
00:13:00,140 --> 00:13:02,250
Monsieur!

247
00:13:02,460 --> 00:13:05,860
This guy's way stronger than he looks!

248
00:13:05,860 --> 00:13:07,430
Speaking of which...

249
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:12,730
You failed at a complete body takeover and went out of control...

250
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:17,140
Enough! Beast Arm Iron Bull!

251
00:13:19,190 --> 00:13:20,810
Lisanna!

252
00:13:20,810 --> 00:13:22,210
I apologize.

253
00:13:22,210 --> 00:13:28,950
But as you were stepping on me previously, I read the gap in your memory.

254
00:13:29,950 --> 00:13:31,450
Why, you...

255
00:13:31,450 --> 00:13:34,320
What a precious little sister of yours.

256
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:37,500
I wonder where she might be now?

257
00:13:37,500 --> 00:13:40,240
Oh, how <i>rude</i> of me.

258
00:13:40,240 --> 00:13:44,890
She's buried in the cold, dark ground, isn't she?

259
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:47,090
Oh, how sad...

260
00:13:47,090 --> 00:13:51,250
How could you do such a cruel thing?

261
00:13:52,370 --> 00:13:55,310
Elf-niichan, my brother?

262
00:14:01,050 --> 00:14:04,570
I won't be deceived... I've got to do this!

263
00:14:04,570 --> 00:14:06,230
Non, non, non...

264
00:14:06,230 --> 00:14:07,860
You can't do that.

265
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:13,310
What would happen if you made a debacle of a full body Take Over, and you lost control?

266
00:14:13,310 --> 00:14:16,920
Did you forget what you did the last time?

267
00:14:16,920 --> 00:14:19,130
Elf-niichan...

268
00:14:19,130 --> 00:14:21,970
How could you forget?

269
00:14:19,930 --> 00:14:23,250
How cruel...

270
00:14:21,970 --> 00:14:25,170
Why?

271
00:14:24,050 --> 00:14:26,550
Don't do it, Elf-niichan...

272
00:14:28,730 --> 00:14:32,260
You shouldn't try to do what you can't handle.

273
00:14:32,260 --> 00:14:37,000
It seems your magical power has weakened considerably.

274
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:38,970
You coward...

275
00:14:38,970 --> 00:14:41,810
If you're a Man, then fight me fair and square, fist to fist!

276
00:14:41,810 --> 00:14:44,550
If I'm a man, you say?

277
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:46,030
Non, non, non...

278
00:14:46,330 --> 00:14:48,360
I cannot let that pass.

279
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:52,570
Not from someone with no right to question the manliness of others.

280
00:14:52,570 --> 00:14:56,670
Trash like you who killed his own little sister!

281
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:59,750
Plâtre Sonate!

282
00:15:06,930 --> 00:15:08,370
Elfman!

283
00:15:09,270 --> 00:15:11,490
Elfman!

284
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,140
What?

285
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:15,410
Why?

286
00:15:15,410 --> 00:15:17,430
Why are you there?

287
00:15:17,770 --> 00:15:19,180
Nee-chan!

288
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:21,540
Oh? So she is your elder sister?

289
00:15:21,540 --> 00:15:27,510
Which means she was once the feared Devil, Mirajane-sama?

290
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:30,570
Lost so much of her magical power...

291
00:15:30,570 --> 00:15:34,700
What a pity! And who could be to blame for it?

292
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:38,720
She is being punished for attempting to deceive us.

293
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:41,210
It won't be long until she is crushed.

294
00:15:42,380 --> 00:15:43,580
Run...

295
00:15:43,940 --> 00:15:46,360
Run, Elfman!

296
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:48,050
Let my sister go!

297
00:15:48,260 --> 00:15:53,030
You will lose your elder sister right before your eyes, just like the younger.

298
00:15:53,030 --> 00:15:59,260
And that is because you are an impotent wizard who does nothing but spout bluffs about manliness!

299
00:16:00,950 --> 00:16:04,460
As a gentleman, I cannot forgive you.

300
00:16:04,460 --> 00:16:07,190
I will give you eternal suffering.

301
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:10,720
Sealing Magic, Merci la Vie!

302
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:12,630
You will become one with the land,

303
00:16:12,630 --> 00:16:17,480
and continue to wander for eternity inside your own unpleasant memories!

304
00:16:19,830 --> 00:16:22,390
No!

305
00:16:32,210 --> 00:16:33,630
That's...

306
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:35,360
Me...

307
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,860
Elf-niichan!

308
00:16:41,860 --> 00:16:43,180
Lisanna!

309
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:45,210
How in the world are you...

310
00:16:46,680 --> 00:16:49,390
Cheer up, Elf-niichan.

311
00:16:49,390 --> 00:16:54,160
It's my fault... It's my fault my parakeet died!

312
00:16:54,160 --> 00:16:55,400
No, it's not!

313
00:16:55,700 --> 00:16:57,930
It's not your fault, Elf-niichan.

314
00:16:58,280 --> 00:17:02,190
Every living thing dies sometime, after all.

315
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:05,850
All living things... die?

316
00:17:05,850 --> 00:17:09,770
Yes. That's the way it is.

317
00:17:09,770 --> 00:17:16,430
But as long as you remember it, that bird will always live on inside your heart...

318
00:17:16,430 --> 00:17:18,720
Inside my heart...

319
00:17:18,970 --> 00:17:20,840
Don't talk like you understand me!

320
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:22,100
Elf-niichan!

321
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:23,220
No more...

322
00:17:30,490 --> 00:17:33,060
Uh, I didn't mean...

323
00:17:33,060 --> 00:17:35,260
Back then, I was...

324
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:37,660
Sheesh...

325
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:39,820
Nee-chan...

326
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:43,140
Fighting again?

327
00:17:43,140 --> 00:17:45,150
Oh, Lisanna... You're back?

328
00:17:45,150 --> 00:17:49,770
Natsu was really mean! He ate all my fish!

329
00:17:48,890 --> 00:17:50,120
Wait...

330
00:17:50,750 --> 00:17:52,960
This time is...

331
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:56,700
Hey, Lisanna, we got a job to do!

332
00:17:57,020 --> 00:17:59,550
But didn't we just come back?

333
00:17:59,850 --> 00:18:04,670
It's an S-class, too! We'll back Sis up on it.

334
00:18:04,670 --> 00:18:06,950
No fair, man!

335
00:18:06,950 --> 00:18:08,400
What kind of job is it?

336
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,110
Emergency Suppression.

337
00:18:10,110 --> 00:18:14,120
We're heading toward the king of monsters, "The Beast."

338
00:18:14,120 --> 00:18:16,770
Natsu, you wanna come with us?

339
00:18:16,770 --> 00:18:18,670
It'll be good experience for you.

340
00:18:18,670 --> 00:18:21,350
Seriously? I'm against that.

341
00:18:21,350 --> 00:18:24,360
A Man should protect his family on his own!

342
00:18:25,140 --> 00:18:27,800
Aw, don't be so stuffy! Take me with you!

343
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:30,360
Don't! Don't go!

344
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:33,690
Or at least, take Natsu with you!

345
00:18:45,530 --> 00:18:48,890
Elfman, hang in there! Wake up!

346
00:18:48,890 --> 00:18:50,350
Elfman!

347
00:18:52,150 --> 00:18:53,730
Elfman!

348
00:18:59,390 --> 00:19:01,320
That's... me?

349
00:19:02,730 --> 00:19:05,120
Elfman, get it together!

350
00:19:05,420 --> 00:19:07,580
Mira-nee!

351
00:19:08,040 --> 00:19:11,900
I evacuated all the people in the town... But what happened?

352
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:13,820
Run, Lisanna!

353
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:15,740
I was careless.

354
00:19:15,740 --> 00:19:20,260
Elfman attempted to protect me, and he tried a Take Over on The Beast.

355
00:19:20,970 --> 00:19:22,340
Then...

356
00:19:22,340 --> 00:19:25,810
However its magical power was too great.

357
00:19:25,810 --> 00:19:27,910
Elfman's lost his reason!

358
00:19:27,910 --> 00:19:29,130
Oh, no!

359
00:19:29,130 --> 00:19:31,810
What'll happen to Elf-niichan?

360
00:19:32,320 --> 00:19:36,840
If he doesn't come to his senses soon, he'll be taken by The Beast!

361
00:19:42,260 --> 00:19:44,550
Lisanna, what are you...

362
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:47,640
Elf-niichan, what's the matter?

363
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:50,000
It's your little sister, Lisanna...

364
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:52,420
Did you forget Mira-nee, too?

365
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:58,300
There's no way that you'd forget us, right Elf-niichan?

366
00:19:58,300 --> 00:20:03,040
Because we both love you very much, Elf-niichan!

367
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,860
Lisanna...

368
00:20:06,860 --> 00:20:07,970
It's no use...

369
00:20:08,280 --> 00:20:11,420
Run!

370
00:20:12,430 --> 00:20:15,500
So, let's go home, 'kay?

371
00:20:16,010 --> 00:20:17,480
Elf-niichan!

372
00:20:40,760 --> 00:20:43,430
It's my fault...

373
00:20:43,430 --> 00:20:45,760
It's my fault Lisanna...

374
00:20:47,110 --> 00:20:48,890
It's not your fault.

375
00:20:50,030 --> 00:20:52,070
Lisanna told you, remember?

376
00:20:52,460 --> 00:20:56,330
Every living thing dies sometime.

377
00:20:57,130 --> 00:21:01,130
You were listening back then, Nee-chan?

378
00:21:01,130 --> 00:21:06,260
Lisanna will live on forever in our hearts.

379
00:21:06,260 --> 00:21:07,740
Isn't that right?

380
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:09,910
N-Nee-chan...

381
00:21:10,860 --> 00:21:14,710
So... We're going to keep on living!

382
00:21:15,230 --> 00:21:16,950
For Lisanna's sake, too!

383
00:21:20,550 --> 00:21:21,940
Nee-chan...

384
00:21:22,270 --> 00:21:23,550
Lisanna...

385
00:21:24,070 --> 00:21:25,640
Elfman!

386
00:21:26,110 --> 00:21:28,510
Elfman, hang in there!

387
00:21:28,510 --> 00:21:32,060
I can't... lose you too!

388
00:21:32,060 --> 00:21:35,760
Now, it's about time for the finale!

389
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,350
Why's that?

390
00:21:37,350 --> 00:21:38,520
Oh?

391
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:42,650
I vowed never to see my sister's tears again!

392
00:21:42,650 --> 00:21:46,300
So what are ya' crying for?!

393
00:21:46,300 --> 00:21:47,900
That light...

394
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:50,780
Don't do it, Elfman! You can't!

395
00:21:50,780 --> 00:21:54,380
Who was it that made her cry?!

396
00:21:54,380 --> 00:21:59,040
It's impossible! You are not capable of doing a full body Take Over!

397
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:03,170
Incredible!

398
00:22:10,010 --> 00:22:11,860
O-Oh, my...

399
00:22:11,860 --> 00:22:13,060
That's...

400
00:22:13,060 --> 00:22:15,220
A full body Take Over!

401
00:22:15,220 --> 00:22:16,860
Beast Soul!

402
00:22:26,740 --> 00:22:27,910
Merry-go-round

403
00:22:27,910 --> 00:22:30,940
I greet the morning,

404
00:22:30,940 --> 00:22:40,560
chasing after your profile left only in my revolving dreams

405
00:22:47,190 --> 00:22:52,940
You said, "I never want to see your face again," when you left me

406
00:22:52,940 --> 00:22:57,870
But the tears on your cheek said it all

407
00:22:57,870 --> 00:23:03,590
Every time you felt like you'd be swallowed up in the waves of contradiction

408
00:23:03,590 --> 00:23:10,470
you always held back your tears, you know?

409
00:23:10,470 --> 00:23:21,490
"What a strong person," they said, but everyone overestimated you

410
00:23:21,490 --> 00:23:30,150
and before you knew it you lost sight of who you really are

411
00:23:30,150 --> 00:23:34,330
Then the sun I thought would always be near me collapsed

412
00:23:34,330 --> 00:23:37,010
and the light shut off...

413
00:23:37,010 --> 00:23:41,160
Rubbing out the truths and the lies of one day, altogether

414
00:23:41,160 --> 00:23:42,570
Merry-go-round

415
00:23:42,570 --> 00:23:45,420
I greet the morning,

416
00:23:45,420 --> 00:23:54,690
still, ironically, chasing after your profile in my revolving dreams

417
00:23:56,560 --> 00:24:00,410
Hey, Happy... It seems like it's raining.

418
00:24:00,410 --> 00:24:04,510
Yeah. Our guild's full of holes right now.

419
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:07,540
With this many holes, there's no lack of leaks in the roof.

420
00:24:07,540 --> 00:24:10,880
Um, it's more like actual rain than leaks...

421
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:14,010
It's got an air of rickety ancient ruins...

422
00:24:14,010 --> 00:24:16,940
Next time: A Flower Blooms in the Rain

423
00:24:16,940 --> 00:24:19,260
We'd better fix it quick before we catch colds!

424
00:24:19,260 --> 00:24:22,100
It's kind of like a giant shower though... Fun!

425
00:24:22,100 --> 00:24:24,690
You take positive thinking too far...

426
00:24:24,690 --> 00:24:27,050


